{"data": {"repository": {"pullRequest": {"id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0MzgwNDYyNTQ2", "number": 1257, "title": "Move exercise hint to new course management routes", "bodyText": "Checklist\n\n I tested all changes and all related features with different users (student, tutor, instructor, admin) on the test server https://artemistest.ase.in.tum.de.\n\nMotivation and Context\n\n\nThe exercise are still managed under the old routes. They should be moved to the new course management routes.\nDescription\n\n\nSplit up hint management and participation components\nImport hint management components in course management module\nUpdate routes of management components\n\nBefore the changes, the hint module got loaded with the code-editor, meaning that you always had to open the editor at least once if you wanted to change or add any hints to a course. We should also have this problem on production. By splitting up the hint modules and having a new dependency in the course management module, we fix this problem.\nSteps for Testing\n\n\nLog in to Artemis\nNavigate to a programming exercise on the course administration\nView the exercise and edit the hints\nYou should be able to add, edit, delete and view hints just like before (and without having to open the code-editor once)", "createdAt": "2020-02-26T19:30:08Z", "url": "https://github.com/ls1intum/Artemis/pull/1257", "merged": true, "mergeCommit": {"oid": "091839ecda60f052faecbdbb4b12e55b8accb755"}, "closed": true, "closedAt": "2020-02-29T09:52:54Z", "author": {"login": "ungaralex"}, "timelineItems": {"totalCount": 6, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABcIL1LZgH2gAyMzgwNDYyNTQ2OjAzYWJlZWM5ZmU4NzkwMGQzMjBmNGZjY2Q3MjUxZDkxM2FlY2FlYWE=", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABcJBch2AFqTM2Njc4OTE0Nw==", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "03abeec9fe87900d320f4fccd7251d913aecaeaa", "author": {"user": {"login": "ungaralex", "name": "Alexander Ungar"}}